  "description": "Amendments to planning permission dated 26 May 2020 (RN: 19/01472) for: 'Excavation to create a deeper basement level and excavation under Wells Mews, demolition of 58-60 Berners Street and demolition behind retained facade of 14-17 Wells Street and erection of a new mixed use development within two adjoining buildings comprising lower ground, ground plus 5 storeys fronting Wells Street and lower ground, ground plus 7 storeys fronting Berners Street to accommodate flexible retail (Class A1) or financial and professional services (Class A2) or restaurant (Class A3) purposes on part lower ground and part ground floors, office (Class B1) on upper floors and installation of plant behind screening on both roof levels.  The scheme also includes external alterations to 14 and 15 Eastcastle Street (part of Woolverstone House) to accommodate a wider and improved entrance into Wells Mews from Eastcastle Street, an upgraded residential entrance to 1 Wells Mews'; NAMELY, changes to the internal layout at lower ground and ground floor levels, removal of bridge and entrance doors to Berners Street retail unit, reduced depth beneath pavement on west side of Wells Mews to accommodate smoke vents, alterations to fenestration, retained roller shutter instead of new louvred access door to Wells Mews, extensions to railings around roof level plant, altered layout of roof level plat and associated alterations.",
